  "title": "Senior/Steel Structural Engineer",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Design, coordinate, plan and manage the projects assigned.</li><li>Plan and oversee ongoing site activities ensuring alignment with project plans.</li><li>Conduct structural analysis to ensure the integrity and safety of the steel elements.</li><li>Liaise with clients, consultants, contractors and relevant authorities to coordinate project requirements</li><li>Ensure all steel members are manufactured and installed according to design specifications.</li><li>Manage and supervise the installation of structural steel components.</li><li>Coordinate with suppliers and manufacturers for the procurement of materials.</li><li>Monitor project progress and provide regular updates to stakeholders.</li><li>Troubleshoot and resolve any issues that arise during the construction process.</li><li>Ensure compliance with health, safety, and environmental regulations.</li><li>Prepare and maintain detailed project documentation, including reports, drawings, and specifications.</li><li>Any other ad-hoc duties as assigned.</li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirement:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Degree in Civil Engineering or equivalent.</li><li>Minimum 3 years of relevant experience.</li><li>Good knowledge of construction methods and regulatory requirements in structural works.</li><li>Strong project management and supervision skills.</li></ul>",
